<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician Guide 1 -40</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">n/a</a> | 
		            12/6/1999 7:37:58 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">So you want to be a magician? Well I hope you like soloing and kiting<BR>
cause thats what magicians do best. With a magicians ability to conjure <BR>
pets and cast high dmg spells we can kill things that are up to 4 levels<BR>
ahead of us. So here is a guide of where to hunt from lvl 1 threw 40 from<BR>
a magician who hunted here myself<BR>
<BR>
This guide starts in qeynos so if your not going to start in qeynos dont <BR>
even bother reading it<BR>
<BR>
1-3 <BR>
Hunt outside of qeynos killed beetles, bats, rats, and snakes<BR>
<BR>
4-7<BR>
at 4 you get your pet, so it will be easier to kill higher lvl things<BR>
so go to qeynos catacombs, kill cubes, beggars, giant spiders<BR>
and giant rats. I know they say beggars lower faction but on all my <BR>
characters i have always killed beggars for a LONG time and never<BR>
even seen a faction change with qeynos<BR>
<BR>
8-10<BR>
at 8 you get your new pet, and 40 dmg spell. So go kill thugs till lvl 10<BR>
I dont know if i was just getting lucky but i was able to take on 2 thugs at a time<BR>
put your pet on both, and cast on one and keep nuking, keep baking up cause they will<BR>
get closer, once you have finished one, the other will be really easy<BR>
after the first hard fight the spawns should be spaced out so drag the thugs out of the room and<BR>
into the hall to your right when one spawns<BR>
<BR>
10-16<BR>
Get a partner (perferable tank or healer) and take on smuggler room. These guys<BR>
give exp all the way till you turn 17, at 14 you should be able to take the smug room<BR>
by yourself with a good weapon<BR>
<BR>
16-19<BR>
at this level you will be advancing to north karanas, a pretty big chance<BR>
since from lvl 4 you been hunting in doors, at north karanas its kinda brings out your<BR>
kiting side. From 16 to 19 kill borer beatles and scyth beetles and the acasional<BR>
griffawn, griffawns might con blue but they are really hard to kill<BR>
<BR>
20 - 27<BR>
at this level go to south karanas, kill elephants, aviaks, and centuars, as your process<BR>
closer to 27 you can advance in the rank of aviaks and centuars you kill, at about 22 to 24<BR>
elephants will stop giving exp, so try and find a group at aviak city or go around killing centuars<BR>
<BR>
27 - 34<BR>
This is pretty simple, go to the basement in highkeep and kill pickclaws<BR>
from 27 to 29 group in warrior or raider groups<BR>
at 29 go to the lookout rooms, i know your asking why go to the lvl 21 lookouts<BR>
when you can be hunting lvl 33 warriors and raiders, well because lookouts<BR>
give lots of exp if you solo them, and with a 29 lvl pet im sure you can solo a lookout<BR>
do lookouts till 31, then go back to raider and warrior groups<BR>
as you advance closer to 34 you will start to gain more exp and faster in the warrior and raider groups<BR>
cause you will generaly be the highest lvl and hog the exp<BR>
<BR>
35 - 40<BR>
head to guk and group, thats about it, just group in guk<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Well this is it, im sure you can follow this pretty easily, so good luck with your mage<BR>
oh yeah, and did you know magicians where the best class in the game? heh well they are because we<BR>
will eventually out damage wizards at higher levels starting at 34<BR>
and we have pets, the only thing bad about a magician, is mages have the lowest hp in the game, so<BR>
make sure and keep yourself buffed!
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
