	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				    Just a few addendums for this guide.  I started a human mage in Qeynos, and did quite a bit of hunting in the Qeynos Catacombs.<BR>
<BR>
  1)  When you are a brand new lvl 1 Qeynosian, you don't really need to risk life and limb in the newbie zone until at least level 3.  There is a freebie quest that gives significant experience from level 1 til 3 or 4.  That is Weleth's broken arrow quest.  I will not discuss the specifics of the quest, but quest info is out there to those who are looking.  Anyway, you will gain positive faction with the guards and merchants, and potentially the SK/Necro guild in Q Catacombs as well.<BR>
<BR>
    2) Once you get your first pet at level 4, just sit down, target any newbie critter that walks by and sic your pet on it.  Down time is minimal, and even though the pet takes half the experience, the kill frequency is high enough that it isn't an issue.  You'll be level 5 in no time.<BR>
<BR>
    3)  Experience on Smugglers thins out a lot by level 14, so you may want to consider hunting the sharks in groups, or make a brief foray to South Karanas or Everfrost to kill Calves.<BR>
<BR>
    4)  Level 16 to 22 you can solo the sharks in Qeynos Catacombs.  Take the right shark out first, med to break up the spawns, then keep alternating sharks every six minutes.  Loot is decent, experience is consistent, and if you get in trouble, you can always just get out of the water to escape.  I used a water pet with excellent results.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
